Have a nice weekend.(祝你周末愉快! )
Good luck.(加油啊!祝你好运! )
Have fun! (祝你玩得愉快。)
Keep it up! (就这样，坚持下去。)
Don't work too hard.(别干得太猛。)
Have a nice trip.(旅途愉快! )
Have a good one! (那多保重! )
I hate to run, but...(真舍不得走，但是…… )
It was nice meeting you. (认识你我非常高兴。)
Please say hello to John (for me). (请代我向约翰问好。 )
Good night. (晚安! )
Come again. (再来啊!)
Don't forget to bring something back for me. (别忘了给我带点儿什么。)
Take it easy. (放松点儿!)
I hope to see you again soon. (希望不久能再见到你。)
Call me later. (给我打电话。)
Take care. (多保重! )
Take care of yourself. (你自己多保重!)
I'll be back. (我还会来的。)
It's getting late. (天不早了。)
I've got to go.(我得走了。 )

●暂时无法见面时
I'll miss you. (我会想你的。)
I wish I could go with you. (我真希望能和你在一起。)
Please give my regards to your family. (请代我向你的家人问好。)
You must come back. (你一定回来啊! )
Give me a call sometime.(有空给我打电话。 )
Let's get together again sometime.(我们什么时候再聚吧。 )
Please write me (a letter).( 请给我写信。) 
I'll write you (a letter). (我会给你写信的。)
Let's keep in touch. (让我们保持联系。)
Don't forget to write. (别忘了写信。)

●拜访
Hello! Anyone home? (喂，有人吗?)
Please come in! (欢迎，请进!)
How nice of you to come! (你能来，太好啦。)
What do you want?(你有事吗? )
Please feel free to make yourself at home.(别客气，像在自己家一样。) 
Have a seat. (请坐吧。)
Enjoy yourself!(您尽兴。 )
Would you care for something to drink?(您喝点什么吗? )
Don't mind me.(没关系。(不用担心我。) )
May I use your bathroom? (我可以用洗手间吗?)
Where's the bathroom?(洗手间在哪儿? )
May I use your phone?(可以借用一下您的电话吗? )
I'd better get going now.(我得告辞了。 )
Thank you for inviting me. (非常感谢您的盛情款待。 )
Drop by sometime. (有空再来串门吧。) 
He came to see me himself.(他亲自来看我。 )
Do you mind if I smoke? (您介意我抽烟吗?)
I like your house. (您的房子真好。)
I really like your apartment.(我很喜欢你的公寓。 )
Watch your step.(小心脚下。 )
The floor is slippery. (地上很滑。  )
Please turn on the TV. (请打开电视。 )
Can I park my car here? (我可以把车停这儿吗? )

●介绍某人
Ms. Kane, this is Mr. Sato, my boss.(凯恩女士，这位是我的上司佐藤先生。) 
Nice to meet you. (很高兴认识您。)
Nice to meet you, too. (彼此彼此。 )
May I have your name, please?(您贵姓? )
I'd like you to meet a friend of mine.(我给你介绍一下我的朋友。 )
He's a nice guy. (他是个好人。)
I'm glad to meet you. (见到您我很高兴。)
It's an honor for me to meet you. (能认识您我感到非常荣幸。) 
Please call me...(请叫我…… )
Don't I know you from somewhere? (我们是不是在哪儿见过面?)
Remember?(想起来了吗? )
Oh, yeah, you're Mr. Smith!(啊!对了，你是史密斯先生。 )
I'm not sure. Maybe.(我不敢肯定，也许在哪儿见过。 )
No, I don't think so.(不，我想不是这样的。 )
This is the first time we have met.(这是我们第一次见面。 )
Is Bob an old friend of yours? (鲍勃是你的老朋友吗?)
I can't remember his name. (我想不起来他叫什么名字了。)
I leave it entirely to your kind consideration. (这事全拜托你了。)
I'm John Sheehan.(我叫约翰·希恩。 )

●和初次见面的人交谈
