 第六章  国外旅游时使用的短句
29在飞机上、饭店里  
●在飞机上
What would you like to drink? (您想喝点儿什么?)
Coffee, please. （请来一杯咖啡。） 
With sugar and cream?（要加牛奶和糖吗?）
What would you like for dinner, beef or fish?（午餐您要牛肉还是要鱼? ）
Beef, please. （请给我牛肉。 ）
Have you finished?（您用完了吗? ）
No, not yet.（ 还没有。 ）
May I clear the table? （我可以收走了吗? ）
Clear the table, please. (请您收拾一下桌子吧。)
Can I have some water?（您能给我杯水吗? ）
Can I have something to drink? （能给我点儿喝的吗? ）
A blanket, please. （请给我一条毯子。）
I feel cold. (我觉得冷。)
I feel hot.（我觉得热。）
I feel sick.（我觉得恶心。） 
Can I have some medicine? （能给我点儿药吗? ）
Could you tell me how to fill out this form? (您能告诉我怎么填这张表吗?)
●在机场
May I see your passport, please? (请出示您的护照。)
How long will you be staying in the United States? (您在美国停留多长时间?)
What's the purpose of your visit?（您来旅行的目的? ）
Sightseeing. （旅游。）
Business。（工作。 ）
I'm here on business. （我是来工作的。 ）
I'm here on vacation.（我是来度假的。 ）
Where are you staying?（您住哪儿? ）
Do you have anything to declare? (有什么需要报关的吗?)
At the Washington Hotel. （在华盛顿饭店。）
How much money do you have? （您带了多少现金? ）
Four hundred dollars and one hundred thousand yen. （我有400美金和10万日元。）
Okay. Have a nice stay.（好了，祝您愉快!）
I can't find my baggage. (我找不着行李了。)
Please check it immediately.（请马上查一查。 ）
Please deliver the baggage to my hotel as soon as you have located it.（找到后请马上把我的行李送到饭店。）
I'd like to reconfirm my flight. （我想确认一下我的机票。）
Where is the Japan Airlines counter?（ 日本航空公司的柜台在哪儿? ）
Where is the boarding gate? （登机口在哪儿? ）
What time do you start boarding? （什么时候开始登机? ）
Has this flight begun boarding?（这个航班开始登机了吗?）
What time will we arrive in Tokyo? (几点到东京?)
●在饭店的服务台
Is there a room available for tonight? (今天晚上有空房间吗?)
I reserved a room for tonight. （我预订了一个房间。 ）
Check in, please.（请办入住手续。 ）
Take my baggage, please. （请帮我拿一下行李。 ）
I'd like a key to room 809, please. （请给我809房间的钥匙。）
Where is the dining room? （餐厅在哪儿? ）
What time does the dining room open? （餐厅几点开门? ）
What time can I have breakfast?（ 几点吃早饭?）
Where can I get some beer? (我在哪儿可以买到啤酒?)
Can you keep my valuables? （我可以把贵重物品存这儿吗? ）
Yen to dollars, please.（我想把日元换成美金。）
Cash, please.（请换成现金。 ）
Could you cash this traveler's check (for me)?（您能帮我把旅行支票换成现金吗? ）
Would you exchange this one hundred dollar bill with five twenties? （请帮我把这100美元换成5张20美元的。）
Does anyone speak Japanese? (有人会说日语吗?)
Are there any messages for me? (有给我的留言吗?)
Check out, please.（我办退房手续。） 
Here's my room key. （这是我房间的钥匙。 ）
I didn't make any phone calls. （我没用电话。 ）
Here's your bill.（这是您的账单。）
Could you call a taxi for me?（能帮我叫一辆出租车吗? ）
●客房服务
Room service, please. （请提供客房服务。）
A wake-up call, please.（请提供叫早服务。） 
Can I borrow a hair dryer? （我可以借一下吹风机吗? ）
Please bring me a pot of coffee. (请送一壶咖啡。)
Laundry service, please. （请提供洗衣服务。）
When will it be ready? (什么时候能弄好?)
Your room number, please. （请告诉我您的房间号码。）
This is room 501. （501房间。*{501的说法是five o one} ）
Come in.（请进。 ）
●在饭店遇到困难时
There is no hot water. (没有热水。)
The room next door is noisy. （隔壁太吵了。）
Could I possibly have another room key?（我能再要一把房间钥匙吗? ）
I locked myself out.(我把钥匙忘在房间里了。)
I'm locked out.（ 我被锁在外面了。 ）
The TV doesn't work in my room. （我房间的电视不能看。）
Could you send someone to fix it? （您能派人给修理一下儿吗? ）
Could you send someone up?（请叫位服务员来一下。）
 
30  走在街上的时候
●问路
Where is the shoe store? (鞋店在哪儿?)
Excuse me, but I'm lost. (对不起，我迷路了。 )
Where am I on this map? (我在地图上的什么地方?)
What's the name of this street?(这条街叫什么名字?)
Is there a post office near here? (这附近有邮局吗?)
How do I get to the Sakura Hotel?(去樱花饭店怎么走? )
Turn right at the first traffic light.(从第一个信号灯往右拐。 )
Where's the rest room? (洗手间在哪儿? )
It's on the right.(在右边。)
Go straight for two blocks. (一直走到第二个街区。 )
You'll see it at the corner on your left. (在左侧拐角那儿就能看见。 )
Sorry, I'm new here, too. (对不起，我也是第一次来这儿。)
It's next to the coffee shop.(在那家咖啡馆的旁边。 )
It's across from City Hall.(在市政厅的对面。 )
It faces City Hall. (正对着市政厅。 )
It's between the bookstore and the drugstore. (在书店和药店之间。)
It's on this side of the church.(在教堂的这一边。)
It's at  of this street. (在这条路的尽头。 )
Am I near Shinjuku?(这儿离新宿近吗? )
How far is it to Shinjuku? (这儿离新宿有多远? )
How long will it take? (要多长时间?)
About five minutes. (5分钟左右。 )
Is it far?(到那儿远吗?)
Not far.(不远。 )
What's the easiest way to get to Shinjuku?(到新宿哪条路最好走? )
The easiest way is to take a taxi.(坐出租车去最容易找到。)
What's the quickest way to get to Shinjuku? (到新宿哪条道最快?)
Where can I mail this? (在哪儿可以发信? )
Where can I make a phone call? (在哪儿可以打电话? )
Is this the shortcut? (这是条近路吗? )
●乘坐交通工具
A subway map, please.(请给我一张地铁图。)
Where's the ticket counter? (售票处在哪儿? )
How much is the fare to Shinjuku? (到新宿多少钱?)
It's one hundred fifty yen. (150日元。 )
Which train should I take to Shinjuku?(到新宿，我该坐哪趟车? )
Where am I supposed to change? (我应该在哪站换车?)
Where am I supposed to get off for Ogikubo? (我要到荻洼在哪儿下车? )
You can change to the JR Chuo Line at Shinjuku. (到新宿换乘JR的中央线。)
Where can I catch an express train? (在哪儿能坐上快车? )
Go to track number two.(到第二站台。)
How often do the trains come?(电车多长时间来一趟? )
The trains come every ten minutes. (10分钟一趟。 )
When is the next express? (下趟快车是几点?)
What time is the last train to Chofu?(到调布的末班车是几点? )
Is the next train an express? (下趟车是快车吗?)
Does this train stop at Chofu? (这趟车在调布停吗?)
It's the fourth stop from here.(从这里数第4站。 )
After the next stop.(下下站。 )
How many stops are there to Shinjuku?(到新宿还有几站?)
What's the next stop?(下站是哪儿? )
The next stop is Chofu. (下站是调布。 )
Where can I get a taxi? (我在哪儿可以打到车?)
Where's the taxi stand?(出租车站在哪儿? )
Call me a taxi, please. (请帮我叫辆出租车。)
How long does it take to get downtown? (到市中心得多长时间? )
How much does it cost?(要花多少钱? )
Where to?(您去哪儿? )
To Wall Street, please. (请到华尔街。 )
To this address, please.(请到这个地址。 )
I'm in a hurry. (我有急事。)
Take the shortest way, please. (请走最近的路。 )
Could you wait for me, please? (请您在这儿稍等一下。)
Stop here, please. (请在这儿停吧。 )
Could you help me carry my bag? (您能帮我拿一下行李吗? )
How much would it cost to get there?(到那儿的话要花多少钱? )
Where's the bus stop? (公共汽车站在哪儿? )
Is there a bus to the airport? (有去机场的汽车吗?)
How many stops to the museum? (美术馆是第几站?)
When is the next bus to Narita? (下趟到成田机场的车是几点?)
Does this bus go to the airport? (这辆车是去机场的吗? )
Could you tell me when to get off? (麻烦您到站时告诉我一声。)
The bus has just left. (汽车刚走。)
The buses don't come on time.( 汽车没有准时来。 )
Is this seat taken? (这儿有人坐吗?)
Isn't the traffic heavy?(路上是不是很堵车? )
●租车
Who should I ask about car rentals? (租车的事，我该问谁?)
